<TITLE> Badiur Rahman goes on LPR Nov 22 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, October 25 (bdnews24.com) The government has accepted former National Board of Revenue chairman Badiur Rahman's application for voluntary retirement. Rahman, and officer on special duty (OSD) with establishment ministry, was informed through a ministerial order Thursday of the decision to grant him one year's LPR to be followed by his retirement on Nov 22, 2008. The directive mentioned as he had completed 25 years of service, he would be granted LPR from Nov 22, 2007 up to Nov 21, 2008 with full pay and facilities to facilitate his voluntary retirement. He would then go into retirement from Nov 22, 2008 and receive pension and other facilities. Rahman was transferred as secretary to the food and disaster management ministry from the NBR on Oct 18. He did not join his new posting, but on the same day applied for a month's earned leave from Oct 22 to Nov 21. On Oct 22, he told journalists in the NBR conference room that he wanted to go into voluntary retirement. bdnews24
